ce:section.ce:para:
The heat transfer coefficient (hnf
                     ) of the system is depending on the working fluids thermal conductivity (knf
                     ). The working fluids thermal conductivity may be depending on the nanoparticle thermal conductivity. Higher particle thermal conductivity leads to enhance the fluid thermal conductivity (Sundar et al. [2]). Among all the nanoparticles carbon related materials knf
                      is larger over other nanoparticles (Sundar et al. [3]). Graphene oxide (GO) comes under the carbon group material with high thermal conductivity, high hardness, and Young's modulus.
